        "title": "Ice melt on Greenland",
        "storyinfo": "Between 2012 and 2016 was the yearly ice loss at Greenland about 247 billion tons, which is a seven-fold increment from 34 billion tons, which was the annual ice loss between 1992 and 2001. \n \n This visualization displays how many melting days Greenland had a specific year between 1989 and 2006. In 2006 Greenland had more melting days than average when comparing it to the other years that have been studied. The blue color in the visualization corresponds to 10 melting days, and the red color corresponds to 60 or more melting days. ",
